cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with deep neural networks in computer vision applications, specifically in domain adaptation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for adapting the statistics in Batch Normalization layers, which falls under the category of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the dependency of DNNs on the training dataset, which is a topic in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with image data, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
